<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54127f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54127f">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54127f"> 127(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ (petre)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Take a little caustic potash solution and add litmus to it, then gently pour some nitric acid in; the blue litmus will soon turn red, because the acid neutralizes the alkali. If the water be now boiled away in a small porcelain basin, a white salt will be left which is nitre or <mark>saltpetre</mark>, <small> H. E. Roscoe, <a name="HERC1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HERC1"><cite title="source">Science Primer: Chemistry</cite></a> (n.d.) 81</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
